{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Set Up Statutory Independent Advocates for Bereaved Families Of Homicide Victims",
        "additional_details": "Families bereaved by homicide face profound trauma but must often navigate complex systems alone. Police FLOs and charities offer support, but cannot act as legally empowered proxies. We feel that grieving families are too often forced to act as legal experts\u2014 battling the IOPC for transparency and managing invasive CICA paperwork. We believe that grief should not be compounded by administrative exhaustion. We want this new statutory right to be known as James\u2019s Law \u2013 to  provide an independent advocate to ensure no family fights these bureaucratic systems alone.",
        "background": "Create a statutory right for families of homicide victims to have a state-funded Independent Advocate. They must be independent of police and legally empowered to act as a proxy for complex administration, including CICA claims and IOPC proceedings.",
